target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopportunities%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20some%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they'll%20have%20to%20get%20into%20their%20parent's%20alma%20mater%20largely%20on%20their%20own%20merits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20way%20colleges%20choose%20to%20admit%20students%20has%20fallen%20under%20intense%20scrutiny.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-colleges-eliminating-legacy-preference-college-admissions-afirmative-action-biden-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court's%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20to%20ban%20the%20use%20of%20affirmative%20action%20in%20college%20admissions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-elite-colleges-legacy-admissions-financial-endowments-alumni-donations-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplaced%20pressure%20on%20many%20prestigious%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20Harvard%2C%20to%20answer%20critics'%20concerns%20that%20favoring%20legacy%20students%20is%20unfair%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20practice%20that%20needs%20to%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20top%20schools%20have%20responded%20to%20the%20high%20court's%20decision%20by%20ditching%20the%20practice%20altogether%2C%20many%20state%20schools%20use%20what%20could%20be%20an%20alternative%20to%20the%20controversial%20practice%3A%20legacy%20scholarships%20and%20awards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fhow-widespread-is-the-practice-of-giving-special-consideration-to-relatives-of-alumni-in-admissions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20think%20tank%20Brookings%20earlier%20this%20month%20found%20that%20most%20state%20flagship%20schools%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20selective%20public%20schools%20in%20a%20state%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20factor%20in%20legacy%20in%20their%20admissions%20processes%2C%20but%20half%20of%20them%20do%20offer%20at%20least%20one%20scholarship%20specifically%20for%20legacy%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%202021-2022%20admissions%20data%20from%20the%20Common%20Data%20Set%20%E2%80%94%20a%20College%20Board%20Initiative%20%E2%80%94%20the%20report%20found%20that%20selective%20and%20private%20colleges%20were%20most%20likely%20to%20use%20legacy%20preference%20in%20their%20admissions.%20When%20it%20came%20to%20public%20flagship%20schools%2C%20more%20than%20one%20in%2010%20consider%20legacy%20status%2C%20and%20half%20of%20all%20flagships%20have%20at%20least%20one%20legacy%20scholarship%20opportunity.%20Those%20scholarships%20could%20range%20from%20%24500%20to%20over%20%2410%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20tangible%20impact%20of%20these%20scholarships%20might%20be%20small%2C%20their%20implications%20could%20be%20larger%20for%20those%20seeking%20to%20attend%20a%20public%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20the%20colleges%20that%20use%20legacy%20admissions%20are%20not%20that%20selective%2C%20and%20the%20scholarships%20for%20relatives%20of%20alumni%20are%20typically%20small%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BStill%2C%20even%20if%20the%20number%20of%20students%20directly%20displaced%20by%20legacies%20who%20had%20a%20leg%20up%20is%20ultimately%20not%20that%20large%2C%20the%20practice%20sends%20students%20the%20wrong%20signal%20about%20what's%20important%20and%20is%20contrary%20to%20the%20mission%20of%20a%20public%20university.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerceptions%20of%20an%20unfair%20admissions%20process%20might%20also%20make%20some%20students%20less%20likely%20to%20apply%20or%20undermine%20the%20perceived%20legitimacy%20of%20higher%20education%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20James%20Murphy%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20higher%20education%20policy%20at%20nonprofit%20Education%20Reform%20Now%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20doesn't%20think%20these%20scholarships%20are%20%26quot%3Bas%20harmful%20a%20practice%20as%20the%20actual%20legacy%20preference%20of%20getting%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20difference%20is%20that%20legacy%20admissions%20give%20a%20leg%20up%20to%20an%20applicant%20who%20may%20or%20may%20not%20have%20gotten%20into%20the%20school%20on%20their%20own%20merit%2C%20whereas%20a%20legacy%20scholarship%20awards%20additional%20aid%20to%20someone%20who's%20already%20been%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurphy%20likened%20scholarships%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20coupon%20or%20discount.%20It's%20to%20get%20you%20into%20the%20store%20and%20buy%20something.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20a%20college%20looks%20at%20students%20who%20are%20legacies%20and%20says%2C%20'Okay%2C%20you%20probably%20have%20a%20better%20chance%20of%20enrolling%20here%20than%20other%20students%20as%20your%20parents%20went%20here%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3B'There's%20a%20family%20connection%2C%20and%20then%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20because%20your%20parents%20have%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20they're%20probably%20in%20a%20wealthier%20income%20bracket.%20So%20that's%20good.%20And%20so%20we're%20gonna%20throw%20you%20%241%2C000%20off.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Brookings%20report%20suggested%20that%20if%20schools%20choose%20to%20consider%20using%20legacy%20status%20for%20scholarships%20and%20in%20the%20admissions%20process%2C%20they%20should%20be%20upfront%20with%20prospective%20students%20about%20what%20that%20means.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20some%20schools'%20messaging%20might%20be%20confusing%20if%20their%20website%20says%20they%20do%20not%20consider%20legacy%20but%20they%20later%20ask%20a%20student%20to%20list%20which%20family%20members%20attended%20the%20school%20on%20the%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegacy%20scholarships%20at%20public%20schools%20come%20in%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20amounts.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20University%20of%20Nebraska%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinancialaid.unl.edu%2Fnebraska-legacy-scholarship-guidelines-2022-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffers%20%2414%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20legacy%20students%20from%20out-of-state.%20Leslie%20Reed%2C%20the%20university's%20public%20affairs%20director%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20scholarship%20is%20awarded%20to%20extraordinary%20out-of-state%20students%20with%20a%20parent%20alumnus%20who%20have%20demonstrated%20academic%20accomplishment%20to%20offset%20the%20cost%20of%20out-of-state%20tuition.%26quot%3B%20Five%20incoming%20first-year%20students%20received%20that%20scholarship%20for%20this%20academic%20year%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20example%20is%20Drake%20University%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Falumni.drake.edu%2Fbenefits%23%3A~%3Atext%3DLegacy%2520Program%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520Drake%2520University%2520Legacy%2520Award%2Cgreat%252Dgrandchildren%2520of%2520Drake%2520graduates.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffers%20a%20%242%2C500%20per%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20award%20to%20legacy%20students.%20A%20university%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20awards%20%26quot%3Bfoster%20and%20maintain%20a%20relationship%20with%20our%20alumni%20by%20encouraging%20their%20family%20members%20to%20continue%20the%20tradition%20of%20attending%20Drake%2C%26quot%3B%20noting%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20hundreds%20of%20gift%20aid%20opportunities%20available%20to%20our%20students.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-elite-colleges-legacy-admissions-financial-endowments-alumni-donations-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20precedent%20continued%20legacy%20preference%20is%20setting%20for%20the%20future%20of%20higher%20education.%20The%20practice%20started%20in%20the%201920s%20as%20an%20effort%20to%20restrict%20the%20number%20of%20Jewish%20students%20admitted%20to%20a%20school.%20While%20some%20colleges%20who%20conti