%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20main%20difference%20I%20observed%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20versus%20the%20army%20was%20that%20everyone%20in%20the%20military%20appears%20to%20be%20working%20toward%20the%20same%20agenda%20and%20objectives%2C%26quot%3B%20Ong%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20everyone%20has%20their%20own%20agendas%20and%20personal%20goals%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20learn%20to%20be%20more%20discerning%20about%20whose%20agendas%20were%20more%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EManaging%20risky%20situations%20in%20the%20military%20could%20help%20you%20navigate%20the%20corporate%20jungle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kwong%20Weng%20Yap%2C%2046%2C%20was%20a%20commando%20with%20the%20Singapore%20Armed%20Forces.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fa9f22895d82203032722b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKwong%20Weng%20Yap%2C%2046%2C%20was%20a%20commando%20with%20the%20SAF.%20Yap%20left%20the%20army%20after%2013%20years%20to%20join%20the%20private%20sector.%3Cp%3EKwong%20Weng%20Yap%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20isn't%20to%20say%20that%20one's%20military%20experience%20isn't%20applicable%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20soft%20skills%20she%20picked%20up%20in%20the%20army%2C%20Ong%20said%2C%20were%20beneficial%20to%20her%20when%20she%20went%20into%20banking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20transition%20to%20DBS%20wasn't%20super%20smooth%2C%20but%20I%20managed%20to%20bring%20in%20certain%20hard%20skills%20and%20soft%20skills%20from%20my%20past%20experiences%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20The%20know-how%20she%20needed%20to%20manage%20stakeholders%20up%20and%20down%20the%20chain%20came%20naturally%20to%20her%20because%20of%20her%20time%20with%20the%20SAF%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-commando-trained-with-navy-seals-it-changed-my-life-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKwong%20Weng%20Yap%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2046%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20tapped%20into%20his%20military%20training%20when%20he%20went%20corporate.%20The%20former%20commando%20spent%2013%20years%20in%20the%20SAF.%20While%20in%20the%20army%2C%20he%20trained%20abroad%20in%20Australia%20and%20the%20US%20under%20the%20Navy%20SEALs%20training%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20SAF%20focuses%20greatly%20on%20efficiency%2C%20operational%20safety%2C%20and%20positive%20results%20and%20outcomes.%20That%20made%20me%20very%20mission-oriented%20and%20mission-driven%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yap%2C%20who%20has%20since%20spent%2011%20years%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20navigating%20the%20corporate%20jungle%2C%20Yap%20likened%20the%20experience%20to%20parachuting.%20Going%20corporate%2C%20he%20said%2C%20meant%20learning%20to%20enjoy%20the%20journey%20without%20losing%20sight%20of%20the%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20gut%20feel.%20The%20ability%20to%20understand%20the%20wind%20conditions%20so%20that%20you%20can%20steer%20your%20parachute%20carefully%20to%20a%20safe%20landing.%20Those%20same%20principles%20apply%20to%20businesses%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Yap%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESome%20people%20think%20veterans%20can't%20cut%20it%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20%E2%80%94%20and%20you'll%20have%20to%20prove%20them%20wrong%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jianhui%20Tan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fa93a84af076d3cf91db4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJianhui%20Tan%2C%2033%2C%20left%20the%20SAF%20in%202021%20after%20serving%20for%2010%20years.%20Tan%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20spent%20six%20months%20taking%20courses%20before%20he%20landed%20his%20first%20full-time%20role%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%3Cp%3EJianhui%20Tan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20military%20veterans%20like%20Tan%2C%20overcoming%20societal%20stereotypes%20was%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20hurdles%20in%20their%20transition%20to%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20told%20BI%20that%20job%20hunting%20was%20difficult%20because%20he%20had%20trouble%20crafting%20his%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20Tan%20said%20he%20couldn't%20talk%20about%20some%20of%20the%20projects%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20during%20his%20service%20because%20they%20were%20confidential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20if%20he%20did%20get%20called%20up%20for%20an%20interview%2C%20Tan%20said%20he%20had%20to%20battle%20the%20negative%20stereotypes%20recruiters%20might%20have%20toward%20former%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mental%20model%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20for%20military%20personnel%20is%20that%20they%20are%20very%20rigid%2C%20they%20do%20not%20have%20any%20relevant%20skill%20sets%20or%20experiences%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20was%20fortunate%20that%20Euromonitor%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20chance%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYap%20faced%20a%20similar%20experience.%20Before%20he%20landed%20his%20first%20corporate%20job%2C%20Yap%20said%20he%20sent%20out%20many%20resumes%20and%20talked%20to%20many%20different%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20former%20commando%20told%20BI%20that%20veterans%20could%20still%20rely%20on%20their%20military%20experience%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%20What's%20more%20important%2C%20Yap%20said%2C%20is%20knowing%20how%20to%20apply%20those%20experiences%20based%20on%20the%20business's%20goals%20and%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20take%20principles%20from%20military%20life%20and%20apply%20them%20in%20a%20different%20context%2C%20like%20business%20operations%2C%20naturally%2C%20not%20all%20of%20them%20will%20be%20relevant%2C%26quot%3B%20Yap%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20times%20when%20you'll%20go%20with%20your%20gut%20and%20times%20when%20you%20need%20to%20think%20objectively%20about%20things.%20You%20just%20have%20to%20be%20very%20honest%20with%20yourself%20about%20what's%20working%20or%20not%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaking%20it%20as%20a%20veteran%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20is%20all%20about%20playing%20to%20your%20strengths%2C%20using%20your%20network%2C%20and%20being%20resilient%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20difficulty%20of%20one's%20transition%20does%20depend%20on%20one's%20prior%20role%20in%20the%20military%2C%20said%20Adrian%20Choo%2C%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20of%20a%20career%20strategy%20consultancy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcareeragility.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECareer%20Agility%20International%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20an%20airforce%20pilot%2C%20then%20one%20of%20the%20clearest%20transitions%20is%20joining%20an%20airline%20as%20a%20pilot.%20But%20what%20if%20you%20are%20an%20explosive%20expert%20or%20a%20naval%20diver%3F%20There%20aren't%20many%20jobs%20out%20there%20that%20are%20relevant%20for%20those%20skills%2C%26quot%3B%20Choo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20navigating%20biases%20like%20what%20Tan%20had%20faced%2C%20Choo%20suggested%20relying%20on%20one's%20network%20when%20job%20hunting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20difficult%20going%20through%20the%20front%20door%2C%20try%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20slip%20in%20through%20the%20side%20door%20by%20asking%20someone%20to%20recommend%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Choo%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BA%20cold%20call%20is%20always%20more%20difficult%20than%20a%20warm%20call.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20Choo%20said%20that%20veterans%20needed%20to%20take%20things%20in%20their%20stride.%20Planning%20ahead%20and%20staying%20resilient%2C%20he%20said%2C%20would%20pay%20off%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20career%20transition%20is%20scary%20and%20painful%2C%26quot%3B%20Choo%20said.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20wait%20till%20the%20last%20minute%20to%20decide%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do.%20Planning%20ahead%20by%20three%20or%20even%20five%20years%20will%20be%20very%20helpful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-army-not-easy-veterans-how-they-did-it-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712019702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f3e9893037f8e81750ac9e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-army-not-easy-veterans-how-they-did-it-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jianhui%20Tan%2C%2033%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20left%20the%20military%20with%20no%20job%20offers.%20He%20spent%20six%20months%20taking%20courses%20before%20landing%20a%20job.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40businessinsider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A162%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-army-not-easy-veterans-how-they-did-it-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20tryst%20with%20terror%20is%20boomeranging%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712019372000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108958101%2Cimgsize-165450.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fwhy-pakistans-tryst-with-terror-is-boomeranging%2Farticleshow%2F108958101.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108958101.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20under%20attack%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Tehreek-i-Taliban%20(TTP)%20that%20operates%20out%20of%20Afghanistan.%20Sachin%20Parashar%20analyses%20the%20problem%20and%20its%2